From c1989b98f65204b93ca176477941f3d5c033e749 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 23:22:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: add support for Airoha AN7563/AN7552 SoC

The Airoha AN7563 (a.k.a. AN7552) is treated here as an EN7581
derivative on the I/O side: chip-SCU and SCU register layouts (in
particular the IOMUX_1 register at chip-SCU offset 0x214) match
EN7581 rather than EN7523. The CPU side, however, is a dual
Cortex-A53 cluster running ARMv8 in 32-bit AArch32 mode, which
keeps the ARMv7-A code path used by EN7523.

To make AN7563 reuse the EN7581 SCU / clock / reset descriptor
tables, the SCU nodes carry both an AN7563-specific compatible and
an "airoha,en7581-{chip-,}scu" fallback. clk-airoha and
reset-airoha already match the EN7581 fallback compatible, so no
new driver-side entries are required for AN7563.

  * Kconfig selects CPU_V7A + ARMV7_SET_CORTEX_SMPEN (no ARM64).
  * arch/arm/mach-airoha/an7563/init.c follows the EN7523 ARMv7
    init shape: fdtdec_setup_memory_banksize(), no armv8/mmu
    mm_region table, direct SCU register write for reset_cpu().
  * arch/arm/mach-airoha/an7563/scu-regmap.c follows the AN7581
    pattern: ofnode_by_compatible() + syscon_node_to_regmap()
    against the "airoha,en7581-chip-scu" / "airoha,en7581-scu"
    fallback compatibles.
  * arch/arm/dts/an7563.dtsi mirrors the EN7581 SCU layout: a
    standalone "airoha,en7581-chip-scu" syscon at 0x1fa20000 and a
    separate "airoha,en7581-scu" clock-controller at 0x1fb00000,
    each preceded by an AN7563-specific compatible. Reset cells
    use EN7581_*_RST IDs so they match the en7581 reset map used
    by reset-airoha.
  * configs/an7563_evb_defconfig clones en7523_evb_defconfig with
    TARGET flipped, default device tree pointed at an7563-evb and
    CONFIG_SYSCON enabled (needed by the regmap helpers).

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
